{
  "stem": "24409.10",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because they took old and dying persons from, from the hospitals, from the old age homes.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They were shipped, too.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they [? gave you ?] [? no tools or ?] nothing.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I knew, but I didn't know anything about the [? sentence. ?] I don't think I visualized much about it.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Although, knew about Dachau from, from people who went to Dachau from Vienna.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But I did not know details.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The first detail I learned was by a prisoner of war who told me that he had served in Russia in one of those units which had buses which killed people in automobiles and vans.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "That's the Jews are killed this way.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was the first, first time I learned.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And then, I was then-- during the Battle of the Bulge, the Germans killed-- you might remember, or you might not know-- 72 American prisoners of war, [INAUDIBLE] prisoners of war in the Battle of Malmedy, near Malmedy.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I now resolved to find [? them. ?] They will be brought to justice.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I was, at the end of the war, with intelligence work not so important anymore, in other areas, with Russia and so on, I was transferred now, at my request, to the war camps branch.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I was assigned to the Malmedy Massacre case as one of the officers.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But I saw right away, this stuff, this is wrong.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "The Americans had American lawyers in charge.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And the American lawyers told the Germans, you don't have-- I'll have to inform you that, you, if you say something which is against you, it will be held against you, and, and so on.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So the Germans very simply said-- didn't speak, didn't say anything.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
